  "decisionNotes": [
    "Frozen historical snapshot — official projects.fivethirtyeight.com/mlb-api URLs no longer serve CSV (redirect away). Resolved file last settled game 2023-06-20, max season 2023. Fine for historical verification; not a live feed for current seasons.",
    "Pitcher-adjusted rating (2014–2023): 57.70% SU, Brier 0.2411 vs plain Elo 56.73% / 0.2429 (n=21773). Third-party writeups often cite ~57.7% — our independent figure is 57.70%, within a couple of points (essentially matching).",
    "Coverage gap inside the freeze: 2023 settled games stop at 2023-06-20 (1330 unsettled rows remain through 2023-10-01). Do not treat late-2023 as fully scored in this file.",
    "All-time aggregate is intentionally de-emphasized (elo 57.80%) — pre-1950 baseball is not comparable to the DH / bullpen era.",
    "Decision leaning: rating system shows a real but modest edge over plain Elo in the modern window (+0.97 pts). Do not rebuild a from-scratch MLB Elo first — use this licensed corpus as the validation benchmark. Because the feed is frozen/dead, it cannot be a live data source; any live MLB model must be independent (no-look-ahead rating updates) and checked against this freeze + real closing lines later.",
    "Opener proxy (2018–2023, |adj|<3 both starters): rating acc low-adj 56.57% (n=251) vs normal 59.06% (n=11665). On the low-adj subset, rating (56.57%) does not beat Elo (56.97%) — consistent with pitcher-adjustment helping less (or hurting) when listed starters carry little rating weight. Sample is small (n=251); treat as a checkable caveat, not proof of opener failure."
  ]
